==Turkish==
[[File:Brooks Chase Ranger of Jolly Dogs Jack Russell.jpg|thumb|bir it]]

===Pronunciation===
* {{tr-IPA}}
* {{audio|tr|LL-Q256 (tur)-ToprakM-it.wav}}

===Etymology 1===
From {{inh|tr|ota|ÿß€åÿ™|tr=it}}, from {{inh|tr|trk-pro|*√ØÃÑt|t=dog}}. Compare {{cog|sah|—ã—Ç|t=dog}}.

====Noun====
{{tr-noun|i|ler}}

# {{lb|tr|chiefly|derogatory}} [[dog]]
#: {{syn|tr|k√∂pek}}
# {{lb|tr|derogatory}} {{l|en|scoundrel}}, [[detestable]] [[person]], [[cur]]

=====Usage notes=====
* Not historically derogatory, and still used as the primary term for "dog" in the countryside. Usually, if a dog is a stray or feral, it can be referred to as "it" as well. The more usual word is {{m|tr|k√∂pek}}, which is also pejorative and derogatory when used for a person.

=====Declension=====
{{tr-infl-noun-c|i|pred=1|poss=1}}

